Subject: 5-Day Gen AI Intensive Course with Google - Now as a Learn Guide!
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We're excited to announce that Kaggle's 5-Day Generative AI Intensive Course with Google is now available as a self-paced Learn Guide! This live event was held from March
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

We're excited to announce that Kaggle's 5-Day Generative AI Intensive  
Course with Google is now available as a self-paced Learn Guide!

This live event was held from March 31- April 4, 2025, and is now made  
available as a self-paced learning guide for anyone interested in  
understanding the fundamental technologies and techniques behind Generative  
AI.





Access Learn Guide Here



This learn guide covers:


Foundational LLMs & Prompt Engineering
Embeddings & Vector Databases
Generative Agents & Agent Companions
Domain-specific LLMs
MLOps for Generative AI


Access whitepapers, podcasts, code labs, and recorded livestreamsâ€”all  
designed to help you build your Generative AI expertise. Join Kaggle's  
Discord to collaborate with other participants.

Happy learning!

The Kaggle Team



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Hi AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA,
Â 
It's no secret that to do well on your GRE, you'll need to work on building your vocabulary. So, how should you go about doing this? Below are some tips to help you make the most of your valuable time and to help you actually learnâ€”and rememberâ€”all of those tricky words!

Step One:Â Use ourÂ vocabulary flashcards ( https://GRE.magoosh.com/flashcards/vocabulary )Â to quickly learn words. These cards should definitely NOT be the only way you
learn words (which we'll explain below), but they're a great start. Be sure to read the example sentences, since it's important to know how to use words in context.

Step Two:Â Read. Read. And read some more. Reading is one of the best ways to improve both your vocabulary and your verbal score in general. Here are some suggested reading materials ( https://magoosh.com/gre/gre-vocabulary-books-recommended-fiction-and-non-fiction/ ). As you read, you should make a list of any new words you see, but doÂ notÂ look up the meanings immediately. Instead, try to infer the meanings from the context.

Step Three:Â Use the dictionary wisely. So, once you've read an article and made a list of words you don't know, you'll need to look the words up. Below are the resources we
recommend:* Vocabulary.com ( https://www.vocabulary.com ): this site provides high quality definitions and example sentences (again: very important!). An alternative is Wordnik.com ( https://www.wordnik.com/ ).
* TheFreeDictionary.com ( https://www.thefreedictionary.com/ ): stuck on a whole phrase and not just one word? Chances are, it's an idiom. This site is a great place to look up the meanings of idioms
* Quizlet.com ( https://quizlet.com/ ): Once you've started compiling a list of words and definitions, you can use this site to make those words into online flashcards. Very useful!
Hope these tips help. Go forth and build that vocab!

Good luck!

Team Magoosh

Subject: Explore Wikimedia's Knowledge with Kaggle!
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We're excited to announce a new collaboration between Kaggle and the Wikimedia Foundation, the nonprofit behind Wikipedia. As part of Wikimedia's mission to make all
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

We're excited to announce a new collaboration between Kaggle and the  
Wikimedia Foundation, the nonprofit behind Wikipedia.

As part of Wikimedia's mission to make all knowledge freely accessible and  
useful, Wikimedia is publishing a beta version of its structured content on  
Kaggle in French and English. This release gives data scientists,  
researchers, and machine learning enthusiasts a new, streamlined way to  
explore and analyze this global information resource. In the spirit of  
democratizing data, you're invited to not only explore the information, but  
to participate in improving and updating it. We're very excited to hear  
what you discover!





Learn More



You can now:


ğŸ” Discover the new Wikimedia datasets
ğŸ“Š Analyze them in Kaggle Notebooks
ğŸ’¬ Join the conversation in our forums
ğŸ“ Download and reuse the data in your own projects
ğŸ“° Read Wikimedia Enterprise's announcement


Let's turn open knowledge into deeper insights.

Happy Kaggling!

Brenda Flynn
Kaggle Partnerships Lead



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Subject: Are You Letting English Steal Your Dream ?
Snippet: Dear M Amrutha Sridhanya, I get it. Taking that next step can be intimidating. But remember why you started this journey. You were tired of feeling stuck in your career because of English. Tired of
Body:
Dear M Amrutha Sridhanya,

I get it. Taking that next step can be intimidating. But remember why you started this journey.

You were tired of feeling stuck in your career because of English. Tired of watching others snatch up those dream opportunities because they spoke better English.

Every day you don't act is another day they're moving ahead. And you? You're standing still.

The IELTS Express Platform is your ticket to catch up. And you can test drive it FREE for 14 days.

[Click here to stop standing still and start moving.](https://careerwiseenglish.com.au/pre-test-checkout/?id=)

Yours sincerely,

Career Wise English

Subject: Tips to manage your parentsâ€™ expectations while studying abroad
Snippet: IDP Logo Find us Sign in SES IDP (1) (2).png Hi M Amrutha Our parents constantly worry about us, and sometimes the pressure can become overbearing. Some concerns are justifiable while some others can
Body:
Hi M Amrutha

Our parents constantly worry about us, and sometimes the pressure can become overbearing. Some concerns are justifiable while some others can be downright unreasonable.Â 

Our expert IDP counsellors are here to help you map a plan to manage their expectations. Here are a few areas to get you started:
1. Education Loan
So, to help you manage funds for your international education, we have partnered with ICICI Bank to offer Smart Education Loans <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4v8cNPkz9gR6_XIxv9VToyb8c3NmZc8VWvj27nETYDS8Q21Zw-bLyBlOy7waOYQeMybc=> to students like you.
2. Accomodation
If you are worried about where you will stay in Australia, donâ€™t be! As always, IDP has got you covered. As part of our Student Essential Services, we help you find your find an accommodation <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4v6ouVOzTkBaW4zrY8IUwveoP1lmAyW7R_PUGvfqA25vtlQ11fcsGT0AtoYKqzGu9Tyc=> in Australia that best fits your needs..
3. Bank Account
Now is the time for you to open and pre-fund a bank account to manage your finances efficiently in the new country. Â To make the process easier for you, IDP has partnered with some of the most credible banksÂ  as part of our Student Essential Services <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4vz6qnERjRHwR5ToWyevxD56-wdJb1jPcdjVkJ25DH03D3fOWNXZ0RpsI_GJ9zg-tjPI=>
4. Heatlh Insurance
Itâ€™s only a matter of time before you start living your education dream. Letâ€™s use this waiting period to get you a comprehensive personal health insurance plan <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4vwYRZFmcCz0ks4v3C-doBfrb6jR32GzaUChjMsc2EomcOvVzrLpSulVchBgSPlWGPsM=>.
As part of our Student Essential Services, we can connect you with credible healthcare services
5. Money Transfer
It is now time to chalk out a plan to send money for your tuition and living expenses to theÂ  Institution. It is important to do this carefully. This is why we have partnered with Cohort Go, Flywire, and Western Union as part of IDPâ€™s Student Essential Services. <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4v6O3p3IBYjpup713XKUUQcBoEfDCfZ_M_q9_iFALPhOD3iWSY4FGjY1yJmb2snB9RwA=>
6. Sim Card
IDP have partnered with telecommunication partners for specific destinations that allow you to access reliable and flexible pre or post-paid sim plans <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4vyTrwtd76Q_BNqoUSjCEqnIiStDMh2bFIlE0sLcPqDxFF5PfoAXpNU8voyhrmFcy4Gs=> that offer you the freedom to choose how you use your mobile device.
Click below to know more about the Student Essential Services.

Dear M Amrutha Sridhanya,

You've come a long way already. You've taken the IELTS Pre-test and faced your English fears head-on. That's fantastic!

But you know as well as we do, that this is just the start. You've got a goal: that dream job in an English-speaking country. A better future. More money. Respect. And you're just one step away from getting closer to it.

Our IELTS Express Platform can help you take that step. And guess what? You can try it FREE for 14 days.

No more feeling inferior to your English-speaking co-workers. No more missing out on promotions. It's time to level up.

[Click here to start your free trial and make that dream job a reality.](https://careerwiseenglish.com.au/pre-test-checkout/?id=)

Yours sincerely,

Career Wise English

Dear Customer,

Date: 11 April, 2025

Indian equity markets managed to close marginally lower during the
week despite extreme volatility in US market.

US imposed a whopping 145% tariff on China (125% reciprocal tariff +
20% fentanyl tariff) and announced a 90-day pause in tariffs for all
the nations except China.

Marâ€™25 US CPI eased to 2.4% vs. 2.8% in Febâ€™25.

RBI cut repo rate by 25 bps to 6.0%; Lowered FY26 GDP growth and
inflation forecast to 6.5% from 6.7% and 4.0% from 4.2% respectively.

Corporate earnings season, tariff related latest developments, US
retail sales & industrial production as well as India CPI data for
Marâ€™25 will be in focus next week.

Subject: AIMO 2025 Progress Prize 2 Competition Wrap-Up!
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, The AI Mathematical Olympiad (AIMO) 2025 Progress Prize 2 competition has officially concluded! This year's challenge asked participants to develop algorithms and models
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

The AI Mathematical Olympiad (AIMO) 2025 Progress Prize 2 competition has  
officially concluded!

This year's challenge asked participants to develop algorithms and models  
capable of solving complex math problems. The competition brought together  
a diverse and talented community, all working to advance AI's capabilities  
in mathematical reasoning.

We're excited to share that participants tackled an even more challenging  
dataset this year and delivered outstanding results. The top performing  
solution achieved an impressive 68% accuracy rate, a significant  
improvement over last year, highlighting the rapid progress being made in  
the field of AI-driven mathematical problem-solving.

To dive into the winning approaches and explore key takeaways from the  
competition, check out the leaderboard and winner solution write-ups below:





View the Leaderboard



Happy Kaggling!

The Kaggle Team



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Body:
Dear Miss. AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA M,

Your account(s) details are available at your fingertips. You can view them online whenever required. For your convenience, please find attached your latest monthly statement.

Your e-account statement is protected by a password, which is the last five digits of customer registered mobile number and date of birth (DOB) in DDMMYY format registered with Bank, for example if mobile number is XXXXX12345 and DOB is 16th September 1982 then password will be 12345160982.

In case of any issues, please lodge a complaint online at contactcentre@sbi.co.in or by calling our 1800 1234 or 1800 2100 toll free numbers or by contacting your home branch.

With Best Regards,
Team SBI

 The Spring Harvest! 

 

 April is an interesting time in the Indian agricultural calendar. In the north and the west, it marks the end of the Rabi season, while farmers in the east get ready to harvest their Boro rice. While much of the south has gathered the dry-season crops, they too celebrate the coming of spring and prepare for a new beginning. In this issue, let us journey through India and discover its springtime traditions. 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

#

 

 

 

1

 

 

 

 

 Crops, Culture & 

 Celebrations 

 

 

 


 

 Punjab erupts in bhangra for Baisakhi. Assam greets Bohag Bihu with a soulful call of the pepa, a traditional hornpipe. In Kerala, people begin the new year with the first sight of Vishukkani, a vibrant display of springâ€™s bounty. Hereâ€™s how every corner of India celebrates the season of renewal. 

 

 

 

 

 
 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

#

 

 

 

2

 

 

 

 

 A Feast Across 

 Regions 

 

 

 


 

 From the fields to your table, explore recipes featuring the freshest yield of the spring harvest. Recreate the delicious flavours of the season in your kitchen, including the saffron-hued Meethe Chawal of Punjab, the tangy, spicy Mango Thokku of Tamil Nadu, and more. 

 

 

 

 
 

 

 

 
 

 

 

 

 

 


#


 

3

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 Be it Bihu or Baisakhi, the new harvest calls for a celebration! Share your recipe for a festival-special dish for a chance to win a bb gift card worth Rs. 500

15 April 2025

Subject: Competition Launch: Yale/UNC-CH - Geophysical Waveform Inversion
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Tuning a radio through static to catch a signal is a lot like analyzing seismic data. You know something important is there, but pinpointing it is the challenge. Geophysicists
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

Tuning a radio through static to catch a signal is a lot like analyzing  
seismic data. You know something important is there, but pinpointing it is  
the challenge. Geophysicists face this daily, searching for what lies  
beneath the Earth's surface.

In this competition, you'll build ML models to improve Full Waveform  
Inversion (FWI), a technique used to map underground structures by  
analyzing seismic waves. The goal is to combine physics and ML to increase  
the speed, accuracy, and reliability of FWIâ€”even with noisy and incomplete  
data.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

June 23, 2025




Learn More



Your work could improve subsurface imaging for renewable energy  
exploration, medical diagnostics, or material analysis applications.

Good luck,

Walter Reade
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

Date: 04 April, 2025

Reciprocal tariff announcement by the Trump administration spooks
global markets.

India at 26% tariff rate, relatively well placed when compared to
Asian peers.

US indices entered bear market territory on growing recession fears.

Market to focus on RBI MPC meeting, Start of the 4QFY25 earning
season, Global cues in a truncated next week.

While the near term volatility is a concern, sharp correction in
commodity prices along with drop in the local bond yields is positive
for Indian equities in the medium term.

Subject: NUS: Outcome of Application
Snippet: National University of Singapore Application Number: N826390244 Programme: IRIS@NUS Dear Miss Amrutha Sridhanya Madduri, We hope this email finds you well. We would like to inform you of the outcome of
Body:
Application Number: N826390244
Programme: IRIS@NUS                        

                          Dear Miss Amrutha Sridhanya Madduri,                        

                          We hope this email finds you well. We would like to inform you of the outcome of your recent application for the IRIS @ NUS programme at the National University of Singapore. We regret to inform you that your application was unsuccessful. The decision is final and no appeals will be allowed.                        

                          We sincerely appreciate your interest in our programme and the time and effort you put into your application. Our selection process was highly competitive, with over 7,000 applications received, which made the decision-making process incredibly challenging.                        

                          Please remember that the outcome of this application does not diminish your accomplishments or qualifications. It is important to recognize that there are many factors involved in the selection process, and the decision does not reflect your potential or abilities.                        

                          We would like to encourage you to keep pursuing your academic and professional goals. We believe you have a bright future ahead, and we are confident that you will find success in your chosen field. If you are entering your final year of study this year, you are very welcome to apply to our PhD and Master's programme at NUS <https://nusgs.nus.edu.sg/programmes/>.                        

                          Thank you once again for considering us and for the time you invested in your application. We wish you all the best in your future endeavors.                        

                          Best Regards,                        

                          NUS Graduate School
                          National University of Singapore                        

This is a system-generated message. Any replies to this message will not be received. Please contact the programme administrator for further assistance.




 National University of Singapore

21 Lower Kent Ridge Road
Singapore 119077
+65 6516 6666

Subject: Competition Launch: Image Matching 2025
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Finishing a puzzle can be hard enough, but what if pieces from other puzzles were mixed in, too? This makes the task even harder since you now have to find only the pieces you
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

Finishing a puzzle can be hard enough, but what if pieces from other  
puzzles were mixed in, too? This makes the task even harder since you now  
have to find only the pieces you need. The same challenge applies to  
building 3D scenes from real-world image sets, where unrelated photos are  
lumped together with relevant ones, complicating accurate scene  
reconstruction.

In this competition, you'll train a machine learning model to sort through  
mixed image collections, group the right ones, and rebuild accurate 3D  
scenes.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

June 2, 2025




Learn More



Your work could improve how we use images in augmented reality, robotics,  
and even scientific research.

Good luck,

Sohier Dane
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

We recommend that you take some time to familiarize yourself with our platform

We look forward to having you in our community.

Dear Customer,

Date: 28 March, 2025

During the week, Nifty50/Sensex extended their winning momentum and
gained 0.7% each while BSE Midcap/BSE Smallcap indices underperformed
the benchmarks closing with loss of 0.7%/1.4% Â respectively.

FII flows were robust during the week as they net bought Rs 27,392 cr
in the cash market while DIIs net sold Rs 849 cr till 27th March.

Trump announced a 25% tariff on imports of automobiles and select auto
components from April 02 which triggered fresh concerns over the
growth of the US economy.

Marâ€™25 Manufacturing/Services PMI for both US and India, monthly
auto sales numbers and quarterly provisional business updates from
banks will be the key things to track next week.

We continue to remain cautiously optimistic on market due to the
recent recovery as well as valuation easing. Investors are recommended
to stick to quality businesses with supportive valuations for medium
to long term investment horizon.

How to manage your folders

To view your custom folders, go to MyÂ Docs > Documents in the header menu. You can conveniently sort files by Type, People, Activity, and Tags.

Create a new folder by clicking AddÂ new > CreateÂ folder in the left-hand menu. Enter the name of your new folder, decide who can access it (make the folder personal or shared), and click Create.

To create a subfolder, click â€œ...â€ next to a parent folder and select CreateÂ subfolder.

Move documents to specific folders by clicking â€œ...â€ next to a file and selecting More > MoveÂ toÂ Folder. Or simply drag and drop a file in the desired folder.

To enable shared access, click â€œ...â€ next to a folder and select ShareÂ folder. Then, specify the contacts with whom you will share access and give necessary permissions.

Subject: Competition Launch: ARC Prize 2025
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We are in an idea constrained world in the race toward true Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). This means conceptual progress can come from anyone. While models today excel at
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

We are in an idea constrained world in the race toward true Artificial  
General Intelligence (AGI). This means conceptual progress can come from  
anyone. While models today excel at processing data they struggle with  
adapting to new challenges. The ARC Prize 2025 competition dares innovators  
to think beyond conventional AI, designing systems that learn and reason  
like humans, unlocking the next frontier of artificial intelligence.

In this competition, you'll build AI systems that can efficiently learn new  
skills and tackle open-ended problems, without relying solely on large  
language models (LLMs) trained on massive datasets. We're challenging you  
to beat the Abstraction and Reasoning Corpus (ARC-AGI-2) benchmark. The top  
submissions will demonstrate progress toward human-like reasoning  
benchmarks.





Total Prizes:

$725,000


Entry Deadline:

October 27, 2025




Learn More



Your work could contribute to new AI problem-solving applicable across  
industries.

Good luck,

Walter Reade
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Dear Customer,

Date: 21 March, 2025

During the week, Nifty50/Sensex/BSE Midcap/BSE Smallcap indices closed
with gains of 4.3%/4.2%/7.1%/7.9% respectively.

FIIs net sold Rs 1,750 cr while DIIs net bought Rs 7,540 cr in cash
market during the week (DII data till 20th March).

Key reasons behind the rally - Supportive global cues, Dovish FED
commentary, Reduced intensity of FII selling, Valuation comfort,
Optimism over ceasefire between Ukraine and Russia and Hope of
earnings recovery in upcoming 4QFY25 result season.

Global cues to dominate next week in absence of domestic triggers.

Investors are recommended to stick to quality businesses with
supportive valuations for medium to long term investment horizon.

Body:
Debt Free Companies

Harness the power of SSL Research!

Dear AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA MADDURI,

At SBI Securities, we believe in empowering you with insights to make
informed investment decisions. In this email, we'll delve into the
attractive characteristics of debt-free companies.

What are Debt-Free Companies?

Debt-free companies are those that operate businesses without any
outstanding debt obligations. These companies have effectively managed
their
finances to eliminate dependence on borrowed funds, showcasing
financial stability and resilience.

What Invest in Debt-Free Companies?

Financial Stability: Without the burden of debt, these companies are
less vulnerable to economic downturns and interest rate fluctuations.

Higher Profitability: Reduced interest expenses can lead to higher
profit margins and increased shareholder returns (Return on Equity).

Greater Flexibility: Debt-free companies have greater flexibility to
invest in growth opportunities, research and development, and
innovation.

Stronger Resilience: These companies are better equipped to withstand
market volatility and economic uncertainties.

Easy Funding for future: These companies generally have better credit
rating profile thus helping it to borrow any future fund requirement
at a competitive rate.

Key Parameters Related to Debt:

Debt-to-Equity Ratio (Total Debt/Equity or Net Worth): Measures the
proportion of debt to equity used to finance a company's assets. A
lower ratio indicates lower debt dependences.

Interest Coverage Ratio (EBIT/Interest): Indicates a company's ability
to cover its interest expenses with its earnings. A higher ratio
suggests stronger financial health and greater ability to service its
debt.

Return on Equity (ROE): Measures a company's profitability in relation
to its shareholders' equity. Higher ROE generally indicates efficient
use of shareholdersâ€™ money.

Subject: Competition Launch: FGVC12 2025
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Put your computer vision skills to the test with this series of research competitions that focus on fine-grained categorization - differentiating between plant or animal species,
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

Put your computer vision skills to the test with this series of research  
competitions that focus on fine-grained categorization - differentiating  
between plant or animal species, for example - that pushes the limits of  
both human and machine performance. You can find these competitions on our  
new community spotlight shelf on our main page.

Help advance image categorization research when you classify marine animals  
into taxonomic categories, identify plants using quadrat images, or  
re-identify animals based on unique traits, among others.





We are excited to host the competitions supporting the Fine-Grained Visual  
Categorization (FGVC12) workshop at the 2025 Computer Vision and Pattern  
Recognition Conference (CVPR 2025) in Nashville, the foremost computer  
vision event of the year.


AnimalCLEF25 @ CVPR-FGVC & LifeCLEF
FungiCLEF25 @ CVPR-FGVC & LifeCLEF
PlantCLEF2025 @ LifeCLEF & CVPR-FGVC
GeoLifeCLEF25 @ CVPR & LifeCLEF
FathomNet 2025 @ CVPR-FGVC


Participate in one or all of the FGVC Competitions to expand the field of  
computer vision.

Good luck,

Maggie Demkin
Kaggle Competitions



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to

change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Body:
MAILER

























Dear Soundarya,




Unlock a detailed understanding of your personality, strengths, and challenges through the holy trinity of Vedic Astrology â€” the In-depth Horoscope, Gem Recommendation Report, and Numerology Report. Together they serve as your ultimate guide for making informed life decisions, exploring relationship dynamics, and fostering spiritual growth.






The In-Depth Horoscope

 gives you in-depth insights into your life by understanding the alignment of planets at the time of your birth. This report offers valuable perspectives on your career, relationships, and key moments in life. With this report, you can learn to enhance favourable planetary influences and mitigate bad fortunes, promoting your overall physical and emotional balance.






The Gem Recommendation report

 lets you achieve prosperity and growth by leveraging the power of gemstones. It identifies the gems that resonate with your unique astrological profile, helping to neutralize negative influences and amplify positive energies. Wearing the recommended gems enhances your vitality and well-being, aligning your energy with that of the planets.






The Numerology Report

 reveals the significance of the numbers related to your birthdate and name. This report provides insights into your personality traits, life path, and potential challenges, fostering self-awareness. Understanding your numerological profile helps you predict life cycles, offering a framework for personal growth and informed decision-making.




Together, these three reports offer you a comprehensive approach to rid yourself of doshas permanently. By integrating these insights, you align your life with the cosmic order, paving the way for a balanced, prosperous, and harmonious existence.

Subject: Competition Launch: BirdCLEF+ 2025
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Mobile and habitat-diverse species play a vital role in tracking biodiversity changes, but traditional observation methods are challenging. With passive acoustic monitoring (PAM)
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

Mobile and habitat-diverse species play a vital role in tracking  
biodiversity changes, but traditional observation methods are challenging.  
With passive acoustic monitoring (PAM) and machine learning, we can now  
analyze audio data to better understand the impact of ecological  
restoration efforts.

This year's BirdCLEF+ competition expands from BirdCLEF 2024 by  
incorporating not only bird species but also amphibians, mammals, and  
insects from Colombia's Middle Magdalena Valley, a critical biodiversity  
hotspot. You'll develop ML models that identify these species by their  
acoustic signatures, with a focus on the limited training data available  
for endangered species.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

May 29, 2025




Learn More



Your work could help researchers track species more effectively and better  
understand the impact of ecological restoration.

Good luck,

Sohier Dane
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Dear AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA MADDURI,

We are pleased to share with you the latest monthly macroeconomic data
report that will provide insights into the current economic landscape.

Key Highlights for the Month:

Consumer Inflation stabilises with month on month decline in food
prices

India Manufacturing PMI hits 5-month high of 57.7 in Janâ€™25

UPI transaction volume at all-time high

Fastag total transaction volume and value grow 14.8% and 19.0% YoY
respectively in Janâ€™25

Gross GST Collection stood at its second-highest level of Rs 2.0
trillion in Janâ€™25, up 13.6% YoY and 10.5% MoM.

Peak Power demand in Janâ€™25 grows to its 7-month high of 237 GW, up
6.6% YoY

Domestic tractor sales grew 11.4% YoY in Janâ€™25, which is seasonally
a weaker month

New Demat account addition at 21-month low; Added 16.5 lakhs accounts
in Janâ€™25 vs average of 31.9 lakhs during last 2 years

Average Daily Turnover in the cash segment stood at its 14-month low
of Rs 1,019 bn in Janâ€™25, down 8.0% MoM and 17.2% YoY

FIIs outflow continues in the month of Febâ€™25; Have sold equities
worth Rs 2.8 trillion during Octâ€™24 to Febâ€™25

Source: SSL Research

Regards,

Team SBI Securities

Dear Soundarya,




Unlock a detailed understanding of your personality, strengths, and challenges through the holy trinity of Vedic Astrology â€” the In-depth Horoscope, Gem Recommendation Report, and Numerology Report. Together they serve as your ultimate guide for making informed life decisions, exploring relationship dynamics, and fostering spiritual growth.

The Gem Recommendation report

The Numerology Report

Understanding your numerological profile helps you predict life cycles, offering a framework for personal growth and informed decision-making.




Together, these three reports offer you a comprehensive approach to rid yourself of doshas permanently. By integrating these insights, you align your life with the cosmic order, paving the way for a balanced, prosperous, and harmonious existence.

Dear Customer,

Date: 13 March, 2025

During the week, Nifty50/Sensex/BSE Midcap/BSE Smallcap indices closed
with cuts of 0.7%/0.7%/2.1%/3.9% respectively on US recessionary fears
and trade tariff war.

FIIs net sold Rs 6,423 cr while DIIs net bought Rs 3,776 cr in cash
market during the week (DII data till 12th March).

US Febâ€™25 CPI data came softer than expected increasing 2.8% YoY and
0.2% MoM. India CPI data eased to a 7-month low of 3.6% in Febâ€™25
vs. expectation of 4.0% largely driven by lower food prices.

FOMC interest rate decision, weekly US jobless claims and India
wholesale price inflation for Febâ€™25 will be key data points to
track next week.

We continue to remain cautiously optimistic on market due to the
recent recovery as well as valuation easing. Investors are recommended
to stick to quality businesses with supportive valuations for medium
to long term investment horizon.

Subject: [Model Launch] Gemma 3 Is Now on Kaggle!
Snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We're excited to introduce Gemma 3, a collection of lightweight open models built on the same advanced technology as Gemini 2.0. Designed for portability and speed, Gemma 3
Body:
Kaggle








Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

We're excited to introduce Gemma 3, a collection of lightweight open models  
built on the same advanced technology as Gemini 2.0. Designed for  
portability and speed, Gemma 3 can run directly on devices, from  
smartphones to powerful workstations, empowering developers to create  
responsible AI applications at scale. With a range of sizes (1B, 4B, 12B,  
27B), you can choose the best model for your needs.





Access Gemma 3



Key Features:


Global support: 140 languages, enabling truly localized AI experiences.
Advanced reasoning: Process images, text, and video with superior AI  
capabilities.
Large context window: 128K-token capacity for complex tasks.
Powerful AI agents: Build intelligent agents with function calling and  
structured output.


Explore the expanding Gemmaverse today and see how Gemma 3 can push your AI  
projects forward.

Brenda Flynn
Kaggle Partnerships Lead



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,

Speakers from Google DeepMind


More info on the event website here.

Hope to see you there!
The Kaggle Team



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

Subject: E-account statement for your SBI account(s).
Snippet: Dear Miss. AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA M, Your account(s) details are available at your fingertips. You can view them online whenever required. For your convenience, please find attached your latest monthly
Body:
Dear Miss. AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA M,

Your account(s) details are available at your fingertips. You can view them online whenever required. For your convenience, please find attached your latest monthly statement.

Your e-account statement is protected by a password, which is the last five digits of customer registered mobile number and date of birth (DOB) in DDMMYY format registered with Bank, for example if mobile number is XXXXX12345 and DOB is 16th September 1982 then password will be 12345160982.

In case of any issues, please lodge a complaint online at contactcentre@sbi.co.in or by calling our 1800 1234 or 1800 2100 toll free numbers or by contacting your home branch.

With Best Regards,
Team SBI

** Please note: You will need Adobe Acrobat to open the attachment. Please do not reply to this email as it is a computer generated email.
